rdf:Description.lla:note: Note in the official log stating that Thomas Edwards was promoted to position of Master upon the dicharge of Richard Watkins.

Birth Place: Nassau New Providence. There is note within the Agreement, stating that a warrant was issued for the apprehension of James C Smith, who was charged with being absent without leave, but was not caught up to time of departure. Account in offical log.

Name identified as 'George' in the offical log. Drowned by falling overboard from the leeward yardarm during a strong gale occasioning heavy squalls and very heavy rain. Full account of drowning in the offical log.
The previous vessel could either be the 'Couch Pearl' or the 'Conch Pearl' - both ships belonged to the port of Nassau at this time.
